answerText: Oculomotor Nerve[10] This other, longest cranial nerve wanders from the brain stem through organs in the neck, thorax and abdomen.

question: Question: For 10 points each, give some important nerves in the human body: [10] Although not the optic nerve, upon entering the orbit this cranial nerve supplies the levator palpebrae superioris and superior rectus muscles, among others, which are responsible for eye and eyelid movement.
